File/Folder			Description
HEAD			Points to the current branch (e.g., refs/heads/main)
config			Repository-specific configuration (e.g., remotes, settings)
description		Used by GitWeb; not important for standard Git usage
index			Binary file that tracks the staging area (files added with git add)
hooks/			Client-side scripts that run at specific events (e.g., pre-commit)
info/			Contains exclude file for local ignore rules (like .gitignore)
logs/			History of changes to branches (logs/HEAD, logs/refs/heads/*)
objects/		All actual data stored here (commits, trees, blobs, tags) using their SHA IDs
refs/			Pointers to commit hashes for branches and tags branches/ (rarely used) Legacy alternative to refs/heads/
